---

<Layout title="Judson Ch.4 — Isomorphisms" favicon="🔗">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/abstract-algebra/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to algebra</a>

    <h1>Isomorphisms</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Tom Judson &middot; GFDL &middot; <a href="http://abstract.ups.edu/">Abstract Algebra: Theory and Applications, Ch. 4</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">An <strong>isomorphism</strong> is a bijective homomorphism. When two groups are isomorphic, they have the same structure wearing different labels. <strong>Cayley's theorem</strong> says every group is isomorphic to a group of permutations, so permutation groups are all there is.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. When two groups are the same -->
    <h3>When two groups are the same</h3>
    <p>Groups G and H are <strong>isomorphic</strong> (written G &cong; H) if there exists a bijective homomorphism f: G &rarr; H. Bijective means one-to-one and onto. Isomorphic groups have the same Cayley table up to relabeling.</p>

    <!-- SVG: two Cayley tables that match up -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 460 200" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Z2 table (left) -->
        <text x="80" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.5">ZZ&#x2082; = {0, 1}#x2082; = (0, 1)</text>
        <!-- Grid -->
        <line x1="30" y1="35" x2="140" y2="35" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="65" x2="140" y2="65" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="95" x2="140" y2="95" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="125" x2="140" y2="125" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="35" x2="30" y2="125" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="67" y1="35" x2="67" y2="125" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="103" y1="35" x2="103" y2="125" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="140" y1="35" x2="140" y2="125" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <!-- Labels -->
        <text x="15" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.4">+</text>
        <text x="85" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="13">0</text>
        <text x="122" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="13">1</text>
        <text x="15" y="85" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="13">0</text>
        <text x="15" y="115" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="13">1</text>
        <!-- Values -->
        <text x="85" y="85" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="13">0</text>
